## Cocke–Younger–Kasami Algorithm

The [Cocke–Younger–Kasami algorithm](/Parsing), more commonly known by its acronyms CYK or CKY, is a parsing algorithm for [context-free grammars](/Context-free_grammar). It was initially published by Itiroo Sakai in 1961, but later rediscovered and named after its independent discoverers: [John Cocke](/John_Cocke_(computer_scientist)), Daniel Younger, [Tadao Kasami](/Tadao_Kasami), and [Jacob T. Schwartz](/Jacob_T._Schwartz). This isn't some flimsy top-down approach; CYK employs [bottom-up parsing](/Bottom-up_parsing) and leverages [dynamic programming](/Dynamic_programming) to dissect a string.

### Class

[Parsing](/Parsing)

